2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 117
BY REPRESENTATIVE DANA HENRY
INSURANCE: Requests the Louisiana State Law Institute to establish a Homeowner
Protection and Efficiency (HOPE) Committee
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana State Law Institute to establish a Homeowner Protection
3 and Efficiency (HOPE) Committee or advisory group to study methods to improve
4 the efficiency, transparency, and fairness of the residential property insurance claims
5 process between homeowners and Louisiana Citizens Property Insurance
6 Corporation (Citizens) following catastrophic losses and to report its findings.
7 WHEREAS, property insurance premiums in Louisiana have increased significantly
8 in recent years, placing a substantial financial burden on homeowners across the state; and
9 WHEREAS, the availability of affordable residential property insurance coverage
10 in the private market has declined, resulting in increased reliance on Citizens, the state's
11 insurer of last resort; and
12 WHEREAS, the structure, financial condition, and operational practices of Citizens
13 directly impact insurance costs, market stability, and the availability of coverage for
14 Louisiana residents; and
15 WHEREAS, Louisiana has suffered extensive catastrophic storm losses in recent
16 years, including Hurricanes Laura, Delta, Zeta, and Ida, resulting in billions of dollars in
17 insured losses and an extraordinary volume of residential property insurance claims; and
18 WHEREAS, homeowners affected by catastrophic storms frequently experience
19 delays in claim resolution, disputes regarding the scope and valuation of losses, inconsistent
20 claims handling practices, and prolonged litigation; and
