1 WHEREAS, timely and fair adjustment of insurance claims is critical to the
2 economic recovery of Louisiana families and communities following catastrophic events;
3 and
4 WHEREAS, prolonged disputes over insurance claims may increase litigation costs
5 for homeowners and insurers, delay rebuilding efforts, and contribute to rising insurance
6 premiums; and
7 WHEREAS, reforms that encourage prompt investigation, transparency in claims
8 handling, fair valuation of losses, early dispute resolution, and efficient judicial
9 administration may benefit both homeowners and Citizens; and
10 WHEREAS, several state and federal courts have implemented case management
11 procedures following catastrophic events in an effort to improve efficiency and reduce
12 unnecessary litigation delays; and
13 WHEREAS, any proposed reforms should balance the need for efficient claims
14 resolution with the constitutional rights of litigants, including meaningful judicial review and
15 access to the courts; and
16 WHEREAS, the legislature recognizes the importance of obtaining input from
17 homeowners, insurers, regulators, legal practitioners, public adjusters, consumer advocates,
18 and other stakeholders regarding potential reforms to the residential property insurance
19 claims process involving Citizens.
20 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
21 urge and request the Louisiana State Law Institute to establish a Homeowner Protection and
22 Efficiency (HOPE) Committee or advisory group to study methods to improve the
23 efficiency, transparency, and fairness of the residential property insurance claims process
24 involving Louisiana Citizens Property Insurance Corporation following catastrophic losses.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the committee or advisory group study methods
26 to reduce unnecessary delay and litigation costs associated with disputed residential property
27 insurance claims.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the committee or advisory group review case
29 management procedures utilized in state and federal courts following catastrophic events.
