1 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the committee or advisory group study evaluate
2 methods to encourage prompt investigation, fair valuation of losses, early dispute resolution,
3 and timely payment of valid claims.
4 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the committee or advisory group study and
5 evaluate topics that include but is not limited to all of the following:
6 (1) Any statutory, administrative, judicial, or procedural reforms that may improve
7 the residential property insurance claims process while preserving the rights of policyholders
8 and litigants.
9 (2) Case management procedures utilized in Louisiana state courts and federal courts
10 following catastrophic events.
11 (3) Claims handling practices involving residential property insurance claims
12 following catastrophic losses.
13 (4) Early dispute resolution procedures and alternatives to prolonged litigation.
14 (5) Methods to encourage prompt investigation and timely payment of valid claims.
15 (6) Methods to improve transparency and consistency in the adjustment and
16 valuation of losses.
17 (7) Methods to reduce unnecessary litigation costs and delays associated with
18 disputed claims.
19 (8) The impact of claims-related litigation and adjustment practices on the
20 sustainability of Citizens and homeowner insurance premiums.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana State Law Institute is requested
22 to invite participation from relevant stakeholder groups, including but not limited to
23 representatives of Louisiana Citizens Property Insurance Corporation, the Department of
24 Insurance, homeowners, consumer advocates, property and casualty insurers, insurance
25 producers, public adjusters, members of the plaintiff and defense bars, and persons with
26 expertise in construction, property damage assessment, underwriting, or judicial
27 administration.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the committee or advisory group may solicit
29 public input and conduct meetings, hearings, or stakeholder discussions as necessary to
30 fulfill the purposes of this Resolution.
